valhistory\"/>\n|Ship commissioned=20 September 1922<ref name=\"uboatnet\"/>\n|Ship decommissioned=early 1930s<ref name=\"navalhistory\"/>\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=yes\n|Ship recommissioned=September 1939<ref name=\"navalhistory\"/>\n|Ship fate=[[Constructive total loss]] 23 December 1943<ref name=\"navalhistory\"/>\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=yes\n|Ship decommissioned=April 1944<ref name=\"navalhistory\"/>\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=yes\n|Ship reclassified=[[Accommodation ship]], May 1944\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=yes\n|Ship recommissioned=June 1945\n|Ship renamed=HMS ''Yeoman'', June 1945<ref name=\"uboatnet\"/><ref name=\"colledge\">Colledge, J. J., ''Ships of the Royal Navy: The Complete Record of All Fighting Ships of the Royal Navy From the Fifteenth Century to the Present'', Annapolis, Maryland: Naval Institute Press, 1987, {{ISBN|0-87021-652-X}}, pp. 385, 386.</ref>\n|Ship reclassified=\n|Ship refit=\n|Ship captured=\n|Ship struck=\n|Ship reinstated=\n|Ship fate=Sold 17 September 1946<ref name=\"colledge\"/> for scrapping\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n|Hide header=yes\n|Ship status=\n|Ship homeport=\n|Ship motto=''In bello in pace fidelis'' (\"Faithful in peace and war\")<ref name=\"navalhistory\"/>\n|Ship nickname=\n|Ship honours=*[[Battle honours#Naval battle honours|Battle honour]]s for:\n*[[Battle of Goodwin Sands|Dover 1652]] (inherited from the first [[English ship Worcester (1651)|''Worcester'']])\n*[[Battle of Portland|Portland 1653]] (inherited from the first ''Worcester'')\n*[[Battle of the Gabbard|Gabbard 1653]] (inherited from the first ''Worcester'')\n*[[Battle of Scheveningen|Scheveningen 1653]] (inherited from the first ''Worcester'')\n*[[Porto Farina|Porto Farina 1653]] (inherited from the first ''Worcester'')\n*[[Battle of Santa Cruz de Tenerife (1657)|Santa Cruz 1657]] (inherited from the first ''Worcester'')\n*[[Battle of Porto Bello|Porto Bello 1739]] (inherited from the third {{HMS|